#: app/templates/help/index.html:139
msgid ""
"Citation counts, open-access status, FWCI, topics, authorships, sources, "
"and institutional links."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:140
msgid ""
"OpenAlex enriches ORCID works; it does not replace the original ORCID "
"metadata."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:143
msgid "Local cache"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:144
msgid ""
"Verified and inferred institution-researcher relationships, synchronized "
"metadata, canonical outputs, run history, and derived quality indicators."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:145
msgid ""
"Cached data makes dashboards and exports reproducible. Inferred "
"relationships remain labeled separately from verified ORCID search "
"results."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:153
msgid "Visibility and completeness"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:154
msgid ""
"A missing work, funding record, or name does not necessarily mean the "
"information does not exist. It may be absent from the source record, "
"private, or not yet synchronized."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:163
msgid "How metadata moves through the platform"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:164
msgid "The complete path from institutional discovery to analytics and exports."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:170
msgid "1. Resolve the institution"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:170
msgid ""
"The registry identifies the institution by ROR and loads any verified "
"GRID and Ringgold identifiers available for broader discovery."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:174
msgid "2. Search ORCID"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:174
msgid ""
"Separate expanded searches are run for each institutional identifier. "
"Results retain their match provenance and are deduplicated by ORCID iD."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:178
msgid "3. Preserve researcher relationships"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:178
msgid ""
"Verified search results are stored before profile downloads. Legacy cache"
" relationships can be backfilled as inferred evidence and remain clearly "
"labeled until a verified search replaces them."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:182
msgid "4. Build ORCID caches"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:182
msgid ""
"Public profile names, works, funding records, and institutional "
"management status are downloaded and stored with synchronization results."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:186
msgid "5. Build canonical outputs and enrich with OpenAlex"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:186
msgid ""
"ORCID work records are linked to a canonical output by normalized DOI or "
"a conservative title-and-year fallback. OpenAlex then enriches eligible "
"outputs."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:190
msgid "6. Present and export"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:190
msgid ""
"Dashboards, quality reviews, institutional comparisons, and downloadable "
"files are generated from the local caches."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:200
msgid "How to read the principal indicators and their limitations."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:205 app/templates/main/index.html:101
msgid "Institutional researchers"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:206
msgid ""
"Unique ORCID iDs related to the active institution. Verified search "
"relationships and cache-inferred relationships are always reported "
"separately."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:209
msgid "Work records and unique outputs"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:210
msgid ""
"A work record is one ORCID source item. A unique output combines records "
"sharing a normalized DOI or, when no DOI exists, a conservative "
"normalized title and year."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:213
msgid "Year-to-date comparison"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:214
msgid ""
"The current year is compared with the same completed months of the "
"previous year. Records without a usable month are excluded from this "
"specific comparison."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:217
msgid "Duplicate candidates"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:218
msgid ""
"Candidate groups use normalized profile names and supporting activity "
"evidence. They indicate cases to review, not confirmed identities or "
"automatic merges."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:219
msgid ""
"Institutional staff may dismiss an unsupported match with a reason or "
"prepare a neutral notice for the researcher. Only the researcher and "
"ORCID can resolve duplicate records."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:222 app/templates/help/index.html:284
#: app/templates/works/cache_status.html:212
#: app/templates/works/cache_status.html:490
msgid "OpenAlex coverage"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:223
msgid ""
"Coverage is the portion of eligible ORCID works matched to OpenAlex. DOI "
"matches are preferred; title matches use strict confidence thresholds."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:226
msgid "Citation and open-access indicators"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:227
msgid ""
"Citation counts, FWCI, topics, and open-access fields come from OpenAlex "
"and reflect its own update cycle and methodology."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:230
msgid "ORCID analytics charts"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:231
msgid ""
"Institutional ORCID charts count cached source work or funding records "
"after applying the visible filters. Timeline charts exclude records "
"without a valid year; they do not silently convert source records into "
"canonical unique outputs."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:234
msgid "Individual researcher charts"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:235
msgid ""
"Profile charts are built from the public ORCID work and funding summaries"
" visible when the profile is loaded. Use the information button on each "
"chart to review its unit, grouping rule, and exclusions."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:239
msgid "Open the duplicate-profile methodology"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:247
msgid "Synchronization, freshness, and exports"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:248
msgid "What an update does and how to evaluate whether a dataset is current."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:252
msgid ""
"A full institutional synchronization discovers researchers, refreshes "
"profiles, works, funding and management status, rebuilds canonical "
"outputs, and enriches eligible works with OpenAlex. Every background job "
"and step is stored with progress and result metadata."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:254
msgid ""
"Use the displayed last-update timestamp rather than assuming a fixed "
"refresh schedule."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:255
msgid ""
"Administrators and managers may start synchronization jobs from the web "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:256
msgid ""
"OpenAlex-only updates also run in the background. Transient failures wait"
" progressively longer before another automatic attempt, while an explicit"
" full refresh bypasses that waiting period."
msgstr ""
"OpenAlex-only updates also run in the background. Transient failures wait"
" progressively longer before another automatic attempt, while an explicit"
" full refresh bypasses that waiting period."

#: app/templates/help/index.html:257
msgid ""
"The interface uses current, stale, running, partial, failed, and empty "
"states consistently across the overview and data-management views."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:258
msgid ""
"Exports are generated from the current local cache and therefore share "
"its update timestamp and limitations."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/index.html:259
msgid ""
"When a verified Ringgold identifier is available, authorized users can "
"download the institution search results used to discover authors; results"
" are deduplicated by ORCID iD."
msgstr ""

